						<p>This record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 953, Pramōda, Āshāḍha, ba. daśamī, Ādityavāra</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1030, June 28, Sunday.</hi> It states that the Noḻamba chief <hi rend="bold">Kanakarasa,</hi> made a gift of 6 <hi rend="italic">mattar</hi> and 100 <hi rend="italic">kamma</hi> of wet land for the service of the god Mahādēva of <hi rend="bold">Arakeṟe.</hi></p>						

